* {{audio|en-us-abjure.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|abjur|ing}}

# {{transitive}} To [[renounce]] upon [[oath]]; to [[forswear]]; to [[disavow]].
#: ''To abjure allegiance to a prince.''
#: ''To abjure the realm'' (to swear to abandon it forever).
# {{transitive}} To renounce or [[reject]] with [[solemnity]]; to [[recant]]; to abandon [[forever]]; to reject; [[repudiate]]; to swear an oath to leave.
#: ''To abjure errors.''
#* '''1610''', ''[[s:The Tempest|The Tempest]]'', by [[w:William Shakespeare|Shakespeare]], act 5 scene 1
#*: But this rough magic I here ''abjure'' [...] 
# {{transitive}} To abstain from.

